list.abstract: feel，英文单词。可做系动词，后常跟省to不定式也可跟形容词或 触觉

yingyinNormal.en: How do you feel? Tired.
yingyinNormal.zh: 感觉怎么样？很累。

yingyinNormal.en: How do you feel? I'm tired.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在感觉如何？累啊。

yingyinNormal.en: How does it feel to be dying?
yingyinNormal.zh: 知道自己快死了是什么感觉？

yingyinNormal.en: So how does it feel to be back here?
yingyinNormal.zh: 回到这儿感觉如何？

yingyinNormal.en: I feel used, not going to lie.
yingyinNormal.zh: 坦白说，我感觉自己被利用了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm sorry. I feel like such an idiot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对不起嘛，我感觉自己就像个白痴。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know, it just doesn't feel like home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也不知道，就是感觉不像家。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, gosh. That makes me feel so special and good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 啊！我现在感觉还真特别真爽啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Phoebe. Yeah? Phoebe, it's okay that you feel this way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 菲比？你有这种感觉也没关系。

yingyinNormal.en: I feel like I should say "Damn." Do it. Damn!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我感觉这句适合喊个"厉害" 。喊吧。厉害！

yingyinNormal.en: Great. I feel like a witch standing over my cauldron!
yingyinNormal.zh: 很好，感觉自己像女巫，站在魔药锅边。

yingyinNormal.en: You don't know what it's like to feel completely frustrated.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不能理解这种闹心的感觉是何滋味。

yingyinNormal.en: She didn't feel anything for him. She loves you. Really?
yingyinNormal.zh: 她对他完全没感觉了，她爱的是你。真的？

yingyinNormal.en: I don't know. I guess I feel comfortable. I'm glad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不知道，大概是和你说话感觉很舒服吧。我很高兴。

yingyinNormal.en: Mom?Yes. I feel everything. What do you mean, sweetie?
yingyinNormal.zh: 妈？什么事？我可以感觉到一切。什么意思，宝贝？

yingyinNormal.en: I feel like I'm five pounds lighter. Really? Only five?
yingyinNormal.zh: 除完我感觉都轻了5磅。真的吗？你确定只有5磅吗？

yingyinNormal.en: They feel hot.
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们让我感觉很热。

yingyinNormal.en: There, is that better? A little bit. Madam Gazelle. Oh, do you feel sick too, Zoe? I might feel sick later, can I sit at front just in case?
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在感觉好点了吗？好一点点了。羚羊夫人。噢，你也感觉不舒服吗，佐伊？我怕我一会儿会感觉不舒服。我能坐前面去吗？以防万一。

yingyinNormal.en: Congratulations. How does it feel to be an all-American? It's an honor, sir. Congratulations. How does it feel to be an all-American? Very good, sir. Congratulations. How does it feel to be an all-American? Very good, sir.
yingyinNormal.zh: 入选全美明星队感觉如何？很荣幸，先生。入选全美明星队感觉如何？很好，先生。

yingyinNormal.en: I thought it would make you feel better when you woke up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我以为它能让你感觉好一点。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 感觉；看法；想法；知觉；对…的悟性；…感；感情；激情；触觉；强烈的感情

word_family.mean: v. 觉得；感到；经受；感受；相信；有一个…印象；认为；同情；怜悯

sense_info_list.zh: 经受; 感受; 感觉

examination_example.sentence: For the low-sympathy kids, how much they shared appeared to turn on how inclined they were to <highlight>feel</highlight> guilty.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对于缺乏同情心的孩子来说，他们分享的多少似乎取决于他们有多容易感到内疚。

examination_example.sentence: We can be prosocial because we caused harm and we <highlight>feel</highlight> regret.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们可以是亲社会的，因为我们会为造成了伤害而感到后悔。

examination_example.sentence: And I <highlight>felt</highlight> like that again, to a certain degree, when people responded to the blog so well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在某种程度上，当人们对博客的反应如此之好时，我又有了这种感觉。

sense_info_list.en: to think or believe that sth is the case; to have a particular opinion or attitude

examination_example.sentence: In fact, rushing to get your own ideas out there can cause colleagues to <highlight>feel</highlight> you don't value their opinions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，急于表达自己的想法会让同事觉得你不重视他们的意见。

examination_example.sentence: It is curious that Stephen Koziatek <highlight>feels</highlight> almost as though he has to justify his efforts to give his students a better future.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不寻常的是，Stephen Koziatek觉得他好像必须要证明自己的努力，是为了给学生一个更好。

examination_example.sentence: We need them to <highlight>feel</highlight> that home can be both here and there and that they can belong to two nations honorably.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们需要他们觉得家可以在这边，也可以在那边，他们可以光荣地属于两个国家。

sense_info_list.en: to experience the effects or results of sth, often strongly

examination_example.sentence: This phenomenon tends to be most acutely <highlight>felt</highlight> during economic downturns and fragile recoveries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在经济衰退和脆弱的复苏期间，(人们)对这种现象的感受往往最为强烈。

word_usage.usage: feel表示某物被摸起来或感觉起来，通常以被摸或被感觉的东西做主语，此时虽有被动意味，但不用被动语态，用主动表被动。

examination_example.sentence: Over the past four months, I had never imagined how I would <highlight>feel</highlight> once our project was completed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在过去的四个月里，我从未想过一旦我们的项目完成，我会有什么样的感受。

examination_example.sentence: As we organized teams, prepared resources and practiced answering questions, I <highlight>felt</highlight> more connected than I ever had to any sports team.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我们组织团队、准备资源和练习回答问题时，我感觉比我与任何运动队的联系更紧密。

examination_example.sentence: Dunn believes that people who reach out to strangers <highlight>feel</highlight> a significantly greater sense of belonging, a bond with others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 邓恩认为，向陌生人伸出援手的人会有更强烈的归属感，形成一种与他人的纽带。

examination_example.sentence: This means that resolving an argument can <highlight>feel</highlight> like you have reached a state of resolution—and you are less likely to be annoyed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这意味着解决一场争论会让你感觉你已经达到了解决的状态——你也就不那么容易恼火了。

examination_example.sentence: We offered to give Sharon a ride home, but she declined, saying that she <highlight>felt</highlight> like walking.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们提议开车送莎伦回家，但她谢绝了，说她想走路。

examination_example.sentence: But after all those years, I found that dance was gradually becoming something that <highlight>felt</highlight> like more of a burden than a joy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是过了这么多年，我发现舞蹈感觉更像是一种负担，而不是一种快乐。

examination_example.sentence: How do the Scotts <highlight>feel</highlight> about moving to Paris?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 苏格兰人对搬到巴黎的感觉如何？

examination_example.sentence: How did the author <highlight>feel</highlight> about joining the OIC project in the beginning?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作者一开始对加入OIC项目有什么看法？

examination_example.sentence: How does the woman <highlight>feel</highlight> about James' situation?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这位女士对詹姆斯的处境有什么看法？

examination_example.sentence: As a matter of fact, I'm <highlight>feeling</highlight> a bit cold.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，我觉得有点冷。

word_usage.usage: 后接名词：The doctor first felt my pulse.大夫先给我把了脉。

接含现在分词的复合宾语：
I felt something crawling up my arm.
我感到有东西在我臂上往上爬。

接含名词的复合宾语：
I felt it my duty to help others.
我觉得帮助别人是我的责任。

接从句：
Feel whether there are any bones broken.
摸摸看有没有骨头断了。

接形容词：
We old workers feel younger too.
我们老工人也感到年轻一些了。

sense_info_list.zh: 抚摸; 触碰; 手感

examination_example.sentence: I like to ride my bike to <highlight>feel</highlight> the fresh air in my face.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我喜欢骑自行车感受迎面而来的新鲜空气。

word_usage.usage:
feel作及物动词时，其宾补可用动词不定式，但通常省略to。
We felt the house shake just now. 
我们刚才感觉房子晃了一下。

feel可以作感官动词，意为“摸起来；感觉”，其后要跟形容词作表语。
如：The silk shirt feels soft.
这件丝绸衬衣摸起来很软。
feel like表示“想要”，其中like是介词，后面可跟名词或动名词，不能跟动词不定式。feel like doing sth表示"想要做某事”。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指用手或手指等触摸某人或某物，强调动作。
指轻轻地触碰某人或某物。
指用手或手指触摸某物以了解其情况，侧重于触摸后的感觉。
普通用词，不如 believe 正式，指细想或思考，也指按自己的思考提出看法、作出判断或得出结论，多用于个人喜好或生活中的实际情况。
通常指依据一定的证据，经思考后认为属实，强调不完全肯定，多为主观上的猜测，不用进行时。
指在作出选择、决定等之前细想，也指经过仔细考虑、观察后而得出比较客观的看法。
尤指根据感觉而不是事实来作出判断。
